7. Results
The machine learning model successfully predicts motor temperature using operational sensor data.
Key observations:
* Motor speed and torque significantly influence temperature.
* Random Forest regression produced the most accurate predictions.
* The deployed Flask application allows users to input parameters and receive real-time temperature predictions.
The system demonstrates how machine learning can assist in predictive maintenance and industrial monitoring.

8. Conclusion
The project Electric Motor Temperature Prediction using Machine Learning demonstrates how AI techniques can be applied to industrial monitoring systems.
By analyzing sensor data and training regression models, the system can accurately predict motor temperature and identify potential overheating risks.
The project followed a structured machine learning workflow including data preprocessing, model training, evaluation, and deployment.
The final system provides an accessible interface where users can input motor parameters and receive real-time temperature predictions.
This solution highlights the importance of predictive analytics in improving equipment reliability, reducing downtime, and enabling smarter maintenance strategies.
Future improvements may include:
* integrating real-time IoT sensor data
* deploying the system on cloud platforms
* implementing deep learning models for enhanced prediction accuracy.

